<TITLE> 'Mugger' beaten dead after killing victim </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, March 4 (bdnews24.com)  An alleged mugger was beaten to death by a mob after he had knifed a man to death at Jiri in Patia upazila on Wednesday. The unidentified miscreant and his accomplices were guised as passengers when they stabbed auto-rickshaw driver Rabiul Alam at around 11 pm. They had taken driver Alam from Bahaddarhat to Patia and stabbed him at Jiri. Locals came forward to rescue him hearing his screams, said Mohiuddin Selim, officer-in-char of Potia Police Station. When the muggers tried to run away the mob nabbed one of them and beat him to death on the spot. Alam succumbed to his injuries on his way to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. He is from Miakhan Nagar under Baklia thana of the city. A case has been filed at Potia Police Station following the incident. 
